items.synopsis: The Magpies have a 25-point lead at the end of three quarters, with the Demons needing a massive final term. Follow the action in our live blog.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: In a quarter that started with an arm wrestle but turned into a shootout, Collingwood have managed to extend their lead. Melbourne should have been further behind at half-time, but they should be closer now after blowing any number of good chances in that third quarter. They have 55 inside 50s to Collingwood's 30, but trail by 25 points. It paints a clear picture of where the Demons have gone wrong. Collingwood haven't lost this year when they've led at 3QT. Melbourne will need something special to buck that trend.
